<HEAD>Schroeder Undecided</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Rep. Patricia Schroeder, D-Colo., who dropped a
brief effort to win the Democratic presidential nomination last
year, doesn't know whether a woman can win the job.
   The problem, she said Monday, is that ``the presidency has become
a series of visuals that I don't know how a woman fits into.''
   Schroeder, who was criticized for shedding tears when she
withdrew from the 1988 race, now keeps a file on the male
politicians who cry in public.
   But she said the voters seem to want strong images that she can't
picture for herself. ``Look at George Bush this summer,'' she said
Monday, in reference to the television and still camera coverage of
his fishing, boating, golfing and jogging.
