<FIRST>r a PM-CerealBurglary     09-12 0337</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Cereal Burglary,0348</SECOND>
<HEAD>Convicted Felon Tries Froot Loop Defense in Burglary Trial</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   If a jury believes Larry Robertson
had Honey Smacks in his cereal bowl, he could spend the rest of his
life in prison. But if it was Froot Loops, he could go free.
   Robertson's attorney has stirred up this confusion in an effort
to clear his client, a four-time convicted felon.
   Robertson, 25, is charged with stealing a rifle and a box of
cereal from a house in Lake Worth on Oct. 15.
   The victim said the pilfered cereal was Sugar Smacks, the puffs
of wheat since renamed Honey Smacks. But a neighbor claims he saw
the thief wearing a red shirt and blue shorts carrying an M-16 rifle
and box of Froot Loops.
   Police never located the rifle, but found Robertson around the
corner, wearing a red shirt, blue shorts and eating a bowl of cereal.
   Robertson said he was eating Froot Loops. Police said they saw
``a puffed-rice type of cereal'' and charged him with burglary and
grand theft.
   ``We all know cereal gets soggy after a minute or two, and it
loses its identity,'' said Robertson's attorney, Michael Lebedeker.
   ``My defense is that the victim said Sugar Smacks, and the
witness saw Froot Loops.''
   When Assistant State Attorney Mark Hanson heard about the Froot
Loop defense, he facetiously named two new witnesses: Toucan Sam,
the cartoon mascot on Froot Loops cereal commercials, and Dig'em,
the hyperkinetic frog for Honey Smacks.
   ``If Dig'em identifies Sugar Smacks, then there goes his
defense,'' the prosecutor said.
   Robertson also is accused of robbing and stabbing a milkman Oct.
6. If he is found guilty of the attack and the burglary at his Oct.
23 trial, he could be sentenced as a career criminal to a life term,
Hanson said.
   ``I'm just going to eat my Wheaties and Lucky Charms and hope the
jury does the right thing,'' Hanson said. ``Then he'll have more
than spilled milk to cry about.''
</TEXT>
