<FIRST>r a PM-People-Reems     09-12 0183</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-People-Reems,0188</SECOND>
<HEAD>Porn Star Reems Pleads Guilty to Tax Evasion Charges</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Harry Reems, who starred in the 1972 hardcore
blockbuster ``Deep Throat,'' pleaded guilty to evading federal
income taxes.
   Reems, whose real name is Herbert Streicher, pleaded guilty
Monday to one count of failing to file a tax return on income of at
least $35,000 in 1982. In exchange, the government agreed not to
prosecute charges that he also failed to file tax returns in 1984
and 1985.
   Reems, 42, faces a maximum penalty of one year in prison and a
$25,000 fine. Sentencing was set for Nov. 13.
   The government contended Reems earned at least $35,000 in 1982
for his work in the porn films ``Society Affairs'' and ``Sometime,
Sweet Susan.''
   Reems acknowledged before U.S. District Judge Consuelo Marshall
that he also faced unspecified state charges. The adult film star
and his attorney, Deputy Public Defender Phil Trevino, declined to
comment on the case.
   Reems, a former Malibu resident who now lives in Utah, is best
known for a role as the inquisitive doctor in ``Deep Throat.''
</TEXT>
