<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     09-12 0531</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0543</SECOND>
<HEAD>Temperatures Drop in North-Central United States</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A huge Canadian air mass early this morning dropped temperatures
to the 30s and 40s across the north-central United States, while
scattered showers fell over the mid-Atlantic states.
   Frost and freeze advisories were in effect this morning for most
of the Dakotas, western and southern Minnesota, northern Nebraska,
northeastern Colorado and portions of Wyoming.
   Light rain extended from the central high Plains across much of
Nebraska into western Iowa, while snow fell in southeastern Wyoming.
Clouds and light rain kept temperatures in the 40s in the central
Plains on Monday.
   Drizzle and light showers also dampened west Texas. Scattered
rain fell across southeastern Missouri and southern Illinois, and
along the mid-Atlantic coast.
   The high for the nation on Monday was 104 degrees at Gila Bend,
Ariz., Yuma, Ariz., and Imperial, Calif.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms scattered
from Florida across the Gulf Coast states to the southern Plains,
over the central and southern Appalachians and portions of Virginia
and the Carolinas; rain or drizzle dampening the central Plains; and
scattered showers across upper Michigan and northern Wisconsin.
   Predicted highs: in the 50s over the central Rockies, the
northern and central Plains and Minnesota, with some readings in the
40s in the central Plains; in the 80s and 90s from the middle and
south Atlantic coastal states across the Tennessee Valley and Gulf
Coast states to most of Texas, in the Pacific Northwest and interior
valleys of California; around 100 degrees in the desert Southwest;
and in the 60s and 70s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 28
degrees at Butte, Mont., to 85 degrees at Phoenix.
   Other reports:
   _East: Albany, N.Y., 59 fair; Atlanta 72 foggy; Boston 69 cloudy;
Buffalo 54 fair; Charleston, S.C., 72 hazy; Chattanooga 73 foggy;
Cincinnati 66 partly cloudy; Cleveland 58 partly cloudy; Detroit 61
partly cloudy; Hatteras 70 hazy; Jacksonville 71 fair; Key West 82
fair; Knoxville 69 foggy; Macon 73 foggy; Miami 80 fair; New York 71
fair; Philadelphia 71 fair; Pittsburgh 63 partly cloudy; Portland,
Maine, 65 cloudy; Richmond 72 foggy; Washington, D.C., 75 cloudy.
   _Central: Birmingham 71 foggy; Bismarck 34 fair; Chicago 61 fair;
Denver 40 foggy; Des Moines 51 cloudy; Fort Worth 71 cloudy;
Indianapolis 65 cloudy; Kansas City 49 fair; Little Rock 71 foggy;
Louisville 66 fair; Memphis 72 foggy; Nashville 71 foggy; New
Orleans 75 partly cloudy; North Platte 38 showery; Oklahoma City 61
cloudy; Omaha 50 rain; Rapid City 39 partly cloudy; St. Louis 66
cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 42 fair; Sault Ste. Marie 56 showery;
San Antonio 77 fair.
