center and began attacking the 25-year-old woman with a knife.
   When Ms. Reed, 45, tried to contact police, a second man demanded
her car keys and told her to get off the telephone, then began
stabbing her and cut the phone line.
   Armed with butcher knives, the men chased the women from room to
room as the victims tried to telephone police or escape.
   The assailants took both women's purses and drove away in Ms.
Reed's car, which was later found nearby, said police.
   The children and mother who witnessed the attack were unhurt,
