<SECOND>PM-Taped Teen,0207</SECOND>
<HEAD>Teen-ager's Foul Mouth Ordered Taped Shut</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A judge had a teen-ager's mouth taped
shut in court for swearing at him during an earlier appearance.
   The 14-year-old stood before Juvenile Court Judge Robert M.
Foster on Monday with his hands cuffed, his ankles shackled and a
5-inch strip of tape over his mouth. He was sentenced to training
school for assaulting three juvenile detention workers during one of
his 13 previous commitments.
   The ``gag order'' was the result of an Aug. 1 hearing. The judge
had ordered the teen-ager held for 24 hours, and he responded with
an obscenity. The judge added 41 days for contempt. The teen-ager
used another obscenity.
   During Monday's hearing, the boy's mother stood beside him. She
said she did not object to the gag.
   ``I told him a thousand times about his mouth,'' she said later.
``When he makes his bed hard, he's going to have to sleep in it.''
   Earlier this year, Foster sentenced a youth to a night in jail
for wearing a T-shirt and shorts to court. Foster requires boys to
wear a tie and trousers and girls to wear slacks or dresses in his
court.
