<FIRST>u i AM-Cuba-PlaneCrash     09-12 0231</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Cuba-Plane Crash,0236</SECOND>
<HEAD>Only Survivor of Cuban Plane Crash Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEXICO CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The only passenger to survive last week's
crash of a chartered Cuban airliner in a Havana suburb has died of
injuries, the Prensa Latina news agency said Tuesday.
   Luigi Capalbo, 22, of Parma, Italy, died Monday at Hermanos
Ameijeiras Hospital in Havana, the Cuban government agency said in a
dispatch monitored in Mexico. The victim had suffered burns over 65
percent of his body.
   The other 114 passengers and 11 crew members were killed when the
Cubana de Aviacion plane crashed into Boyeros, a residential area a
half-mile from the Havana airport on Sept. 3. The agency earlier
said 45 people were killed on the ground, but Tuesday's dispatch
gave the number as 24.
   Reports on the number of injured varied. Prensa Latina said
Tuesday some remained in serious condition, but gave no figures.
   The plane was carrying Italian tourists on a flight to Milan when
it crashed shortly after taking off in a thunderstorm.
   A preliminary report on the investigation said the pilot took off
against advice from the control tower.
   Capalbo had traveled to Cuba with three friends from his minor
league baseball team to watch Cuban teams play. Reports from Rome
said he worked for a private detective agency. Prensa Latina said he
was a first-year law student at the University of Parma.
</TEXT>
