<HEAD>People in the News</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: SUBS last graf in Pittsburgh-dated item to CORRECT spelling
of name to Elsie, sted Else.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   There's nothing like being on a first-name
basis with George Bush _ even if the president doesn't always get
the first name right.
   Pittsburgh industrialist Henry Hillman, whose wife, Elsie, is on
the Republican national committee, received videotaped
congratulations from President Bush on Monday night as he was named
the Pennsylvania Chamber of Commerce's 1989 Business Leader of the
Year in Hershey.
   ``Henry, you've made a difference all your life. You're a model.
I'm proud to call you friend,'' Bush said.
   But Hillman admitted the president called him something else when
he recently sent a picture of himself and Barbara Bush.
   ``It was signed from George and Barbara Bush, with our best
regards, to Elsie and Harvey Hillman,'' he said. ``It was one of
those wonderful things in life.''
</TEXT>
