<DOCNO> AP890912-0180 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-09-12-89 1921EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>u w AM-Gregg-RollCall     09-12 0374</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Gregg-Roll Call,300</SECOND>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is the 66-33 roll call by which the Senate
Tuesday confirmed the nomination of Donald Gregg to be U.S.
ambassador to South Korea.
   On this vote, a yes vote was a vote to confirm while a no vote
was a vote to reject the nomination.
   Voting yes were 21 Democrats and 45 Republicans.
   Voting no were 33 Democrats and 0 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
   Adams, D-Wash., no; Armstrong, R-Colo., yes; Baucus, D-Mont.,
yes; Bentsen, D-Texas, yes; Biden, D-Del., no.
   Bingaman, D-N.M., no; Bond, R-Mo., yes; Boren, D-Okla., yes;
Boschwitz, R-Minn., yes; Bradley, D-N.J., no.
   Breaux, D-La., yes; Bryan, D-Nev., yes; Bumpers, D-Ark., no;
Burdick, D-N.D., no; Burns, R-Mont., yes.
