<HEAD>30 Students Killed When Wall Collapses</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Thirty students were killed and another 25 injured
when a wall collapsed while the youths were watching a show outside
their middle school in China's coastal Fujian province, the official
Xinhua News Agency said Wednesday.
   The news agency said the disaster occurred Sunday evening at the
No. 1 Middle School in Liancheng County, where about 4,000 people
had gathered for activities marking the 75th anniversary of the
school.
   It said the 65-foot-long structure collapsed, crushing those
below, when people climbed on top of it for a better view of the
show.
   In China, middle school students are aged 12 to 18.
   Premier Li Peng sent a message of condolence to families of the
victims, Xinhua said.
