<FIRST>r f PM-Drexel-Charges     09-12 0181</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Drexel-Charges,0190</SECOND>
<HEAD>Summary of Charges Contained in Drexel Guilty Plea</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Drexel, Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a synopsis of the six felony counts to which the
investment giant Drexel Burnham Lambert Inc. pleaded guilty Monday:
   1. Securities fraud for the fraudulent filing of required
disclosure documents, known as Schedule 13Ds, in connection with the
Pennsylvania Engineering Corp. takeover of Fischbach Corp.
   2. Mail fraud for the manipulation of MCA Inc. common stock
during Golden Nugget Inc.'s sale of its MCA holdings.
   3. Securities fraud for unlawfully aiding disgraced stock
speculator Ivan F. Boesky defraud regulators and Boesky's creditors
and investors through an stock ``parking'' scheme involving Phillips
Petroleum Co. common stock.
   4. Securities fraud for more false Schedule 13D filings in the
Boesky organization's purchase of Harris Graphics Corp. common stock.
   5. Securities fraud for the manipulation of Stone Container Corp.
common stock during a convertible securities offering that was
underwritten by Drexel.
   6. Mail fraud for the manipulation of the price of C.O.M.B. Corp.
common stock in connection with a convertible securities offering
underwritten by Drexel.
</TEXT>
