<HEAD>Nissan Knocks Back Price of New Stanza</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The 1990 Nissan Stanza sedan will cost $749, or
about 6 percent, less than the 1989 version of the car, the Japanese
automaker says.
   Robert Thomas, vice president and general manager of the Nissan
Division of Nissan Motor Corp., said Monday manufacturing
improvements and design changes enabled the automaker to cut the
base price of the Stanza XE to $11,450.
