<FIRST>r f BC-WPP-Seiniger     09-12 0257</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-WPP-Seiniger,0267</SECOND>
<HEAD>WPP Group Agrees to Buy California Entertainment Ad Agency</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   WPP Group PLC, the British-based advertising and
marketing services giant, said Tuesday it has agreed to buy Seiniger
Advertising Inc., a Los Angeles-based agency that specializes in
marketing movies.
   The deal calls for an initial payment of $10 million in cash and
stock and additional payments of up to another $20 million in cash
and stock based on the agency's financial performance over the next
four years.
   Seiniger was launched in 1974 and has marketed over 650 movies,
including campaigns for the movies ``Bull Durham,'' ``Indiana Jones
and The Last Crusade,'' ``Jaws'' and ``The Untouchables.''
   The announcement said senior management of Seiniger Advertising,
including founder and president Tony Seiniger and executive vice
presidents Michael Kaiser and William Manger, have signed long-term
service contracts.
   The London-based WPP said the acquisition will strengthen its
presence in the fast-growing field of entertainment marketing, which
it said amounted to $1.4 billion in the United States last year and
is growing at a 20 percent annual rate.
   WPP already owns JWT Entertainment Group, which markets motion
pictures, entertainment videos and television programming from
headquarters in Los Angeles and New York.
   WPP is the second-largest advertising and marketing services
holding company in the world behind Saatchi &amp; Saatchi Co., also
based in London.
   Its holdings include the advertising companies J. Walter Thompson
and Ogilvy &amp; Mather Worldwide; the public relations firm Hill and
Knowlton and an assortment of market research, marketing services,
design and specialty advertising firms.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
